  "title": "Electrical Engineer, Construction/M&E",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate Electrical works and services for building construction projects (M&amp;E contractor environment)</li>\n  <li>Plan, develop, and manage work schedules to ensure tasks are completed on time.</li>\n  <li>Prepare progress reports for clients and project managers, detailing delays, defects, and necessary rectification measures for Electrical works</li>\n  <li>Report on Electrical works progress and arrange site inspections with contractors, subcontractors, and clerk-of-works.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with safety and health regulations, striving for a zero-accident work environment and maintaining high housekeeping standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 1-3 years of relevant experience in the construction or M&amp;E Contracting industry</li>\n  <li>Diploma/NITEC in Electrical, Electronics or relevant engineering disciplin</li>\n  <li>Basic knowledge of Project execution processes.</li>\n  <li>Advanced knowledge of local code of practice of design implementation.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the role resonates with you and your professional experience complements the responsibilities listed, send your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p>\n<p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p>\n<p>bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
